OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1774033868
OL,3,CITV News on the frontline with police
OL,4,Cdismantling county lines crime networks
OL,6,FCounty lines is a type of organised
OL,7,Fcrime in which gangs from large cities
OL,8,Fexpand their drug networks into
OL,9,Fsmaller towns and rural areas using
OL,10,Fdedicated phone lines. They often
OL,11,Fexploit vulnerable people, including
OL,12,Fchildren and those in financial
OL,13,Fdifficulty, to transport and sell
OL,14,Fdrugs.
OL,16,FThis can involve coercion, threats and
OL,17,Fviolence. Victims may be forced to
OL,18,Ftravel long distances or stay in
OL,19,Funfamiliar places a practice sometimes
OL,20,Fcalled 'cuckooing', where criminals
OL,21,Ftake over someone's home.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/6
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
